om, establishing its enduring connection with knowledge and insight.</p><p>=
Many Native American traditions view the owl as a powerful spirit guide and=
 keeper of sacred knowledge.</p><p>In modern contexts, the owl often symbol=
izes intelligence, intuition, and the ability to see what others cannot. It=
s ability to turn its head nearly 360 degrees has made it a symbol of persp=
ective and the ability to see beyond the obvious.</p><p>In popular culture,=
 the owl frequently appears as a wise mentor figure, reinforcing its associ=
ation with knowledge and guidance.</p><p>New Age spirituality often invokes=
 the owl for developing psychic abilities and navigating life=E2=80=99s mys=
teries.</p><div style=3D"height:20px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-bloc=
