e have spirit animals.</p><p>If I had not traded face-to-face with my custo=
mers and relied on online sales, I would never have known why people buy my=
 art. It gave me invaluable insights into what motivates the public.</p><p>=
The jaguar, with its immense strength, holds a revered place in the spiritu=
al and symbolic traditions of the Americas. In Mayan mythology, the jaguar =
was associated with the night sun and the underworld, representing transfor=
mation and spiritual journey.</p><p>Many Amazonian cultures view the jaguar=
 as a symbol of power, ferocity, and valor. The Aztecs had =E2=80=98jaguar =
warriors=E2=80=99, elite fighters who would wear jaguar skins and masks int=
o battle.</p><p>Shamanic traditions often invoke the jaguar spirit for heal=
ing and protection. The jaguar=E2=80=99s ability to see in the dark has lin=
ked it to the ability to navigate through life=E2=80=99s mysteries.</p><p>I=
n modern spiritual practices, the jaguar is often called upon for its stren=
gth and courage.</p><p>Its role as an apex predator has made it a symbol of=
 confidence and assertiveness and an icon for rainforest preservation.</p><=
div style=3D"height:20px" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"wp-block-spacer"></=
